to come up with a plan.

00:41:23.850 --> 00:41:27.400
The same thing has to happen in
other areas of climate change

00:41:27.400 --> 00:41:30.620
impact with precipitation, and
flooding, and things like that.

00:41:30.620 --> 00:41:33.320
I don't think it's happening
yet because one of the drivers,

00:41:33.320 --> 00:41:36.600
here in New England,
as we are a home rule

00:41:36.600 --> 00:41:38.980
place-- so every
town has jurisdiction

00:41:38.980 --> 00:41:41.855
over their own things--
and people don't always

00:41:41.855 --> 00:41:43.980
like to work with other
people because, number one,

00:41:43.980 --> 00:41:45.396
it's kind of
overwhelming to think

00:41:45.396 --> 00:41:47.310
about dealing with
somebody else's problem

00:41:47.310 --> 00:41:49.100
when I can barely
deal with my own.

00:41:49.100 --> 00:41:52.050
But I think we're going to
have no choice but to move

00:41:52.050 --> 00:41:53.986
towards that.

00:41:53.986 --> 00:41:55.360
But I don't think
it's happening.

00:41:55.360 --> 00:41:57.693
It's beginning to happen, but
it's not happening as much

00:41:57.693 --> 00:41:59.480
as it should, probably, yet.

00:41:59.480 --> 00:42:02.890
But the more we talk
about this stuff, it will.

